motions.motion_text:
WHEREAS the City of Ottawa’s Housing Acceleration Plan Section 4A identifies emerging policy levers for the strategic use of public lands for affordable housing development;
WHEREAS housing cooperatives, both provincial and federal are an important component of the City of Ottawa’s local affordable housing ecosystem;
WHEREAS the City of Ottawa has entered into land leases with housing co-operatives to enable those co-operatives to construct residential buildings and operate on City lands;
WHEREAS housing co-operatives are well positioned in both the preservation and creation of affordable housing within the City of Ottawa;
WHEREAS co-operative boards are independent and self-determining;
WHEREAS the City is afforded an opportunity to engage with co-operatives as lease approach renewal;
WHEREAS the City’s Disposal of Real Property Policy requires that municipal lands be disposed of at market value unless otherwise authorized by Council;
THEREFORE BE IT RESOLVED THAT staff be directed to develop a guiding document for housing co-operatives to be made available well in advance of the end of lease terms, outlining steps to take and potential supports available for co-operatives interested in exploring options for developing new affordable housing on their sites;
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that this document be developed in consultation with relevant housing sector partners that may include but are not limited to local housing cooperatives, CHF Canada, CHASEO, and the Ottawa Community Land Trust;
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED THAT this document be submitted to Committee and Council for consideration no later than Q1 2027.
